left class=m><span class=title>   Tactics</span><hr size=1> It's been a while since I did this so I can't remember exactly how I got through but I don't remember doing anything special for it. I think I just used my usual tactics to be honest. I rarely used summons and never cloudkill (too cheesy) with this group. <br>
<br>
There is hugely wrong with the balance of your party by the way and your main character's class (Cavaliar) is particularly useful here. Although your group does suffer from lack of a pure cleric, potions of extra-healing are (too) easily available in ToB so in-fight healing isn't a big deal. Yes, from a powergaming point of view it's possible to make a far stronger party (in particular by introducing a sorcerer) but this is a moot point <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
As for tactics, I would suggest making liberal use of the following:<br>
<br>
Stoneskin &amp; Iron Skins:<br>
At maximum casting level, both of these spells are obscenely powerful (too powerful really). Stoneskin on <br>
the mages should greatly help with the archers.<br>
<br>
Jaheira:<br>
Don't be fooled by her comparatively low level. She makes a mean tank if you gear her up for it and give her Greater Whirlwinds (spend some of your druid ability points on them too - an undocumented benefit of being multi-classs). Equip her with the fully upgraded Staff of the Ram and she can be as good as any primary tank, better in fact because of her Ironskins (of which she will have many at max level). <br>
<br>
Minsc:<br>
If you're not doing so already I find Minsc works best if you forget he is a ranger and just consider him to be a sturdy (and amusing) tank. Give him full plate (or dragon scale), dual wield Crom Faeyr and another weapon that gives nice immunities and he tanks just fine.<br>
<br>
Summons:<br>
In general I prefer not to use them but that's purely a personal preference. Exceptions though are the high level abilities to summon Devas, Planetars and (especially) Elemental Princes (druid only). These are too potent to ignore for big fights and should be used here.<br>
<br>
Healing:<br>
As I alluded to earlier, don't bother healing during combat, with the possible exception of Mass Heal. It's far more effective to load up on Potions of Extra-Healing in ToB. Strange as it seems, High level clerics are probably more useful for their offensive capabilities at this level than their healing.<br>
<br>
Insect Swarm:<br>
Jaheira again heh. Annoyed by enemy casters? Barring magic resistance, this is THE spell for dealing with them.<br>
<br>
Chaotic Feedback:<br>
On everyone if you can to avoid nasty mind based attacks but buff your melees with it at a minimum.  There are also a couple of weapons around that provide similar benefits to this spell.<br>
<br>
Cloak of Mirroring on your main tank:<br>
Will effectively take the beholders out of the equation if you run him into the fight first.<br>
<br>
Greater Malison + Chaos:<br>
Since you you have three magic-based casters, take advantage of this and have one or two of them debuff while the third drops an offensive spell. For example, try this combo: Have one drop Greater Malison on the enemies while the other hits them with Chaos and a third drops Horrid Wilting (excellent spell because it won't hurt your tanks). This can turn hard fights into a joke.<br>
<br>
Contingency:<br>
I often had it set to trigger Stoneskin on my mages when their health got low. Two lots of Stoneskin should be enough to get even the wimpiest mage through the fight.<br>
<br>
Spell triggers:<br>
Greater Malison and Lower Resistance are particularly useful against demons and triggers can allow you to fire these off immediately. Also, having a couple of rounds of instant-cast magic missiles can be pretty effective for dropping annoying casters (once you've done the obligitary stripping of buffs).<br>
<br>
Time Stop:<br>
You mentioned your group was maxed so Imoen at least should have this by now. Very, very powerful, especially if your mage is wearing the Robe of Vecna for faster casting time.<br>
<br>
Staff of the magi:<br>
Kinda cheesy but this item gives your mage permanent improved invisibility if I recall. Equip it and enjoy being able to cast at your leisure<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Improved Invisibilty:<br>
Buff everyone with this.<br>
<br>
And the usual buffs like Improved Haste of course.<br>
<br>
Those are a few of the things I used, there are many more <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
